             was indicted for <rs id="t18250915-258-off1386" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18250915-258-off1386" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-258-off1386" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18250915-258-cd1387" type="crimeDate">8th of August</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-258-off1386 t18250915-258-cd1387"></join>, a coat, value 12 s.; a waistcoat, value 5 s.; a pair of trousers, value 5 s.; a pair of boots, value 14 s.; four handkerchiefs, value 16 s.; a cap, value 1 s., and nine shillings, the property of 
                     <persName id="t18250915-258-victim1314" type="victimName">
                        John 
                        Rice
                     <interp inst="t18250915-258-victim1314" type="surname" value="Rice"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18250915-258-victim1314" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18250915-258-victim1314" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-258-off1386 t18250915-258-victim1314"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , in his dwelling-house
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>JOHN RICE. I live in <placeName id="t18250915-258-crimeloc1388">Compton-place, Brunswick-square</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-258-crimeloc1388" type="placeName" value="Compton-place, Brunswick-square"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18250915-258-crimeloc1388" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-258-off1386 t18250915-258-crimeloc1388"></join>; I only lodge there, and am a <rs id="t18250915-258-viclabel1389" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18250915-258-victim1314 t18250915-258-viclabel1389"></join>. On the 2d of August the prisoner came to inquire for work; he worked at my own room two days. On the 4th my wife and child died; I gave him sixpence, and told him to get work till after the funeral; he slept in my house on Sunday, the 7th, in the same room as me; the clothes which I wore on Sunday were in the room; next morning about five o'clock I got up; he was gone, and the clothes also; he had left his own behind; I did not see him again till the 3d of September, when he was taken at the fair with my coat and trousers on.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-258-person1315">
                  WILLIAM 
                  JOHNSON
               <interp inst="t18250915-258-person1315" type="surname" value="JOHNSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-258-person1315" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-258-person1315" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer, and took the prisoner on the 5th of September, at Bartholomew Fair; Rice's son was with me; he had this coat and trousers on.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18250915-258-person1316">
                  PEARCE 
                  RICE
               <interp inst="t18250915-258-person1316" type="surname" value="RICE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-258-person1316" type="given" value="PEARCE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18250915-258-person1316" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner at my father's house, and slept in the same room with him. On the 5th of September I saw him at the Fair; I and my cousin went up to him, and had him taken.</p>
               <p>(Coat and trousers sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner pleaded distress.</p>
               <p>
